Description:
  Generate a custom UntitledUi theme CSS file with color overrides.

  A theme overrides CSS custom properties (brand, error, warning, success,
  and gray color scales) scoped under a CSS class, so you can switch themes
  by toggling that class on <body>.

Usage:
  rails generate untitled_ui:theme THEME_NAME [--preset=PRESET]

Arguments:
  THEME_NAME  - The name of the theme (e.g. corporate, ocean, dark).
                This determines the CSS class name (.corporate-theme)
                and the output file name (corporate.css).

Options:
  --preset    - Optional. Use a curated color preset instead of
                placeholder values. Available presets:
                  corporate - Professional blue-gray palette
                  ocean     - Cool blue-teal coastal palette
                  warm      - Warm orange-earth tone palette

Examples:
  rails generate untitled_ui:theme corporate
    Creates app/assets/tailwind/untitled_ui/corporate.css with placeholder
    colors and adds the import to application.css.

  rails generate untitled_ui:theme ocean --preset=ocean
    Creates app/assets/tailwind/untitled_ui/ocean.css with curated ocean
    color values pre-filled.

  rails generate untitled_ui:theme dark --preset=corporate
    Creates a theme named "dark" but seeded with the corporate color preset.

Applying a theme:
  Add the theme class to your <body> tag:
    <body class="corporate-theme">

  To switch themes dynamically with JavaScript:
    document.body.className = 'ocean-theme';
